ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If the defense pool has fewer than four dice when I use this power, but then the defender adds defense dice to their pool using their own battle plans, do I get +2 attack dice?
A:  No. You check this at the moment you use the power.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Why would I kill one of my own warbands?
A:  To refresh more Supply during your Rest Phase.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If I'm a Citizen and the Chancellor holds the Darkest Secret, do I get this bonus?
A:  Nope. "You" means you personally (Rule 10).

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I swap this with a locked card?
A:  Nope. A locked card cannot be discarded, moved or swapped.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How many exchanges can this prompt?
A:  As many as you want.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does "any Exile" include myself?
A:  If you're an Exile, yes!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this count if I target a pawn at a site with an Order card?
A:  No, you have to target the site itself. Of course, if you target a site and other things, this power takes effect.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this power stack with Mushrooms?
A:  Yes. Guess he knows where all the good mushroom spots are.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this Supply gain stack on top of powers that let me spend no Supply?
A:  Yes! You'll end up gaining Supply by campaigning in this case, not losing it.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does the killed warband remove a second attack die?
A:  Nope, you've already collected dice. You lose one warband and one attack die, exactly.

Q:  Does the killed warband count for Cursed Cauldron?
A:  Yes!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I take favor if the bank only has one left?
A:  Yes!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If I sacrifice the last warband from a site, can the attacker still take it?
A:  Yes. They've already targeted it.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I use my other Trade modifier powers before using Master of Disguise?
A:  No, you fully replace your advisers with another player's advisers for the current Trade action.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I take someone's last secret? Most cards don't allow this.
A:  Yup! You're giving them favor, after all.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I kill one at a site and one at another site, or one at a site and one on a board?
A:  Yes, you can mix and match however you want.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  When can I use this power when traveling to its site?
A:  If you rule the site.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this let me draw two cards with Mushrooms?
A:  Yes. Guess you know where the good stuff is.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  When exactly do I pay for this power?
A:  When you choose to use it, immediately after someone takes relics and they're in your region.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does taking burned favor include if someone recovers a relic from a site with a favor burn cost? What if I'm the one recovering it?
A:  Yup, you take the favor in all of those cases.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If there are no warbands at the site I travel to, do I have to kill a warband on my board?
A:  Nope. It's one at the site.

Q:  Can I still travel to a site if there are no warbands there?
A:  Yup. That's what the "if able" signifies (Rule 10).

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I play a card facedown as long as I play the other to a site?
A:  Yes!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I use Palanquin to go to a site with Toll Roads?
A:  Yes, but the player whose pawn is at your site must choose to give a favor to Toll Roads' ruler, if they don't rule it themself. If you rule Toll Roads, they must choose to give a favor to you--how generous, right?

Q:  If we're both at the Shrouded Wood, who chooses where we go?
A:  You will always go to the site that you choose, as long as the other player could travel there. If you rule the Shrouded Wood, you choose their destination, which can be different from the site that you go to. If they rule the Shrouded Wood, they will travel to the same site as you. If a third party rules the Shrouded Wood, the third party will choose where the player travels.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If I'm the Chancellor and I'm joining a campaign as an Imperial Ally to a Citizen defender, does using this battle plan mean that the Citizen defender can't use other battle plans?
A:  No. "You" refers to you alone, not your Imperial Allies (Rule 10).

Q:  If the bandits rule Code of Honor as well as other battle plans that they can use, which battle plans will they use when defending in a campaign?
A:  They will use Code of Honor and no others.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Wait, can I make a deal with an Exile if I'm a Citizen?
A:  Sure can.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this work with Imperial Allies if I'm the Chancellor?
A:  The "you" in this power, and all others, means you alone (Rule 10). It does not count Imperial Allies.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this include the Conspiracy?
A:  Yup!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does the "unless your enemy has the People's Favor" restriction apply to both the skull cancellation and attack dice?
A:  Yes, the entire power is canceled if your enemy has the People's Favor.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this interact with Pied Piper?
A:  Since Pied Piper ignores the adviser limit, you can have any number of Nomad advisers, Pied Piper, and one card other than Pied Piper.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this card mean I can have four advisers?
A:  Yup!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this include itself in the number of nomad cards ruled?
A:  Yes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does the cost include any secret cost added by Gleaming Armor?
A:  Yes.

Q:  Does this include the Buried Giant and The Hidden Place site powers?
A:  Yes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this increase the Visions Drawn track?
A:  Yes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Is the card discarded if I choose +/-1 attack die?
A:  No, only if you choose +/- 3.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does my attack roll include skulls?
A:  Yes. Basically, act as if you got all your dice results twice.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this interact with the Careless trait?
A:  You still don't get the favor from Careless.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this count things like the Oathkeeper bonus and defense dice added by battle plans?
A:  Nope, Giant Python specifies that it only counts defense dice added by declaring targets, which the Oathkeeper bonus and battle plans are not.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Does this card stack with powers like Augury and the Greedy trait?
A:  Yes!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  What if I don't have any warbands?
A:  Not a problem. You only kill one if you have any on your board.

ContainedObjects.Nickname: Hall of Debate / Hall of Mockery
ContainedObjects.Name: Card
Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this interact with the Fertile Valley?
A:  If you play a Hearth card to the Fertile Valley, you will get one secret (for playing to a site) and one favor (for playing to the Fertile Valley specifically).

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this interact with Hospital?
A:  Warbands that would be killed are placed on Hospital's site, as long as that player still rules it. Then, any warbands in that player's force are put on Obsidian Cage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can the Chancellor use this?
A:  Yes! The other players should probably think about getting the Skeleton Key away from the Chancellor.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  What cases does this cover?
A:  All of them! You can campaign against sites but you can't place warbands at them. You can't drop off warbands using a minor action (Rule 6.5). You can't use Warning Signals to move warbands around. And so on.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If I have the Bandit Crown, can I take the last warband off my site as a minor action (Rule 6.5)? Likewise, can I simply put a warband on a site with no warbands on it?
A:  Yes to both! The bandit there counts as your warband, so you're not really taking your last one off the site, and you rule empty sites.

Q:  In the Chronicle, if I won, do I discard empty sites?
A:  Nope! You rule them.

Q:  In the Chronicle, if I won as the Chancellor, and a Citizen has the Bandit Crown, do I discard empty sites?
A:  Yes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  So if I'm in The Hidden Place, can I force them to flip over a secret to travel to me?
A:  Yes!

Q:  If they're in another region and the Narrow Pass is in my region, will Whistle work?
A:  Nope. They won't be able to travel to you.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  Can I use this if my region's discard pile is empty?
A:  Nope!

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  How does this interact with Hospital?
A:  Hospital prevents warbands from being killed, so you don't gain warbands for them.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Q:  If I sacrifice the last warband from a site, can the attacker still take it?
A:  Yes. They've already targeted it.

A:  To refresh more Supply during your Rest Phase.
